<HEADLINE>
3-year-old boy dies after shot in head in Flint
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FLINT, MI -- A 3-year-old boy shot Friday night in Flint has died, police said.
The child was taken to Hurley Medical Center around 9 p.m. Friday, Oct. 13 with a single gunshot wound to the head and originally listed in critical condition.
Witnesses told police the shooting happened in the area of North Dort Highway and Carpenter Road.
Anyone with information is asked to call Flint Police Detective Sgt. Alfino Donastorg at 810-237-6919. Tips can be made anonymously by calling Crime Stoppers at 1-800-422-JAIL (5245) or at P3tips.com.
